'''Axioche''' {{IPAc-en|ə|ɡ|ˈ|z|aɪ|ə|ˌ|k|iː|,_|æ|ɡ|-}} (Άξιόχη) was a [[nymph]] in [[Greek mythology]]. She was the mother of [[Chrysippus (mythology)|Chrysippus]] by [[Pelops]].<ref>[[Scholia]] on [[Euripides]], ''Orestes'', 4; on [[Pindar]], Olympian Ode, 1. 144</ref> Elsewhere she is referred to as "Danais".<ref>[[Pseudo-Plutarch]], ''Greek and Roman Parallel Stories'', 33</ref>

